      • BruteForce

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> BruteForce()
        Solution for Two Sums algorithm. Solution ~O(n^2).
        Returns:
        Two element integer array. Example: nums = [3, 5, 9, 6] target = 9 returns [0, 1] because [Index 0] + [Index 1] = 3 + 5 = 9

      • Optimized

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> Optimized()
        Solution for Two Sums algorithm. Limits the use of arrays and lookups are down via a HashMap Solution ~O(n).
        Returns:
        Two element integer array. Example: nums = [3, 5, 9, 6] target = 9 returns [0, 1] because [Index 0] + [Index 1] = 3 + 5 = 9
